    "This is true even if an AI Monitor is not human, but could be formalized as any agent including AIs of different capabilities.The argument for unmonitorability of advanced AI systems could be made based on dependence of monitorability capability on other impossibility results, such as unexplainability, unpredictability and incomprehensibility of AI [112], but in this paper we will present a number of independent arguments for Unmonitorability of AI.",
    "Types of monitoringIn the context of AI safety, monitoring can be classified into several types, each focusing on different aspects of AI system behavior and performance.",
    "A proposed taxonomy for AI safety monitoring follows:1.",
    "Functional monitoring Functional monitoring refers to tracking the AI system's performance in terms of its intended tasks and objectives.",
    "This type of monitoring is crucial for evaluating the system's efficacy and ensuring that it meets its functional requirements [21]."
